[Old prepared data file|https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1fohHT6-dQUlPMK6dAf5YQhkJNLL3txOk/edit?gid=1186154814#gid=1186154814]
Started with a Long Form that had candidate mismatches and major LF vs Stat vote differences. I first fixed candidate matching using party-aware and fuzzy-name logic, then traced the remaining high diffs to shifted Form 20 Excel source data. I directly converted and parsed the original Form 20 PDFs through automation, rebuilt the affected constituency source files, updated the canonical Long Form, and regenerated {{validation.html}}, resolving the major error constituencies ({{9}}, {{16}}, {{25}}, {{51}}) within the same day. This also removed the need to assign PDF Form 20 conversion separately to Extractor or DEOs, avoiding both manual extraction work and coordination delay. Overall, the automation saved roughly {{16-24 hours}} including execution and follow-up effort.

Note: Required Extraction of NOTA for all ACs and Some Missing Candidates AC wise done directly by me. 

